tion. A modest discount is enough to keep present, measurable global health competitive with future-protecting work; remove it (the next assumption) and the astronomical numbers take over. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_3.drawio" id="w1_2_3"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2e3b3;strokeColor=#c9a72a;fontColor=#57450e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="27" y="239" width="172" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;▼ 19 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5.drawio" id="w1_2_5"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5d3b8;strokeColor=#cc7a33;fontColor=#5a300e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="73" y="478" width="200" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Suffering-focused&lt;br&gt;ethics&lt;br&gt;[1+2+6]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Pearce)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + suffering_focused&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Asymmetry: averting intense suffering takes priority over creating happiness. Factory farming, malaria and the worst wild-animal conditions weigh up; speculative future-flourishing bets weigh down. Arises most naturally from taking animal suffering seriously, so it requires animals_somewhat. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 6 suffering_focused" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJydWNty2zgS%2FZUu126t5BIliuOrUn7wRU5S8ex4Y894d22XA5GQiBFJMABomsn43%2FcA1NWSYmefTJPA6dON7j4Nfd%2BK%2BJAViTmVEd%2FqbXU6dHR0RNeKiYyMpFCxbxUeyozuisDv7lApVRI9Cl5S2X0IHvaooY3Maa9pN95lADjWukhzI2RGYQycHvmUMyXDWLDEwnQPA%2BrSkKkHVrLqIS5Slunph4BYJlKW6ActU17GzEy%2F7JEuhkOuRDZ6GMqw0Dxy9vosjInNjQpNjC4rE%2BN5KBJOcGX%2BWXfIWFAWRbpFisN%2FkXFNUjkwxT1wZSk3MKTx3sS8duMfmoZFFjqMdxTKNJcaVOYLsDeLOBDxSmiHpg3LIpbIjFOKACdt%2BjKLX%2F%2Fxi6Vqt%2FOnnIcGGx9ZUnCSQ4cwD3XbgZ1wbWhQVFRYM3aj5ouO9egaWB9sNDldcDYqeL3xff%2Bf%2Fc%2FH1%2F0zGlQ04hlXzPB2Xk2PlEfCLEVoGx9blElT87BBBJLD%2Bj0LuTLW21QqHOcsWLpeW0eC5XkiuG7TVZW2EznKpMKRNr7nuy3KD3efmw7LHdSh%2F3c6%2FfjOrRxww%2Bq3uZIDNhCJMCAykNbjyObjrd%2Bi7n2bzlloJGwyxWsoLMht%2BDPTIi2J25yQaoRD69%2BWZ8cX%2F%2Bn87Z4GPJElEs%2FudYfLn%2FCcVNgObATUYcF2VISmPgYcHEd2wv1hIgvsinHmZ0KH4GToaNVBZHvbP3Bu2seD5yaRyytgwoeSi1EMbNSG4szYBIoRLZuCmhrXMmVajN%2FRH3DIfgv8wEewZol%2FqQSom2q95W67OzG8196dGOZPRrEFs%2BwR52eh4TPPkEEz7M3mXVjOhEKSEsfq0CEtxDhXKFlVIcAZyikUeG7RSf%2F8t8%2F9Ok8cQk0CuJvzYloRs29UxhIkTSk9LaJJxdc5Y9feTnbeT3OZZaCE8vDk0EvZKBOmiDid%2FHbdP0ViVOlAJiJ0GYI4VA7NHnCjOUkOm30ZSyqDVSiT2BUaQDVL84RH7brb1F4PxahQaC91rY%2FUJE1t54QLGukSojUIW9i2LRkkEV7mn4QJY55dcgnEDzzJeXTJ1e862phOu7N0cqWzAHLDk2TAEdL3KLsz8N6I4XdnIH73BcqpTWaubGEULDlh2fgP14hqrCITQ2A1fJtdoLC81xqd0f%2Bxe9v0Q%2Bbb1OiSR6%2FzqrtHbEyue51OWZbtkXjkJQDbOJiOTWyVMdvKWNIxPIwzEeIJdT1Cs9KdkOnYQ